   "source": [
    "# DEPOXY Protocol Analysis - LEPLAT Allan\n",
    "## Shoe Condition Comparison During Running\n",
    "\n",
    "### Protocol Overview\n",
    "The DEPOXY project investigates the peripheral energy expenditure during locomotion with different shoe models.\n",
    "\n",
    "**Test Protocol:**\n",
    "- **Initial baseline phase**: Rest before exercise\n",
    "- **6 running blocks** of 5 minutes each\n",
    "- **5 recovery blocks** of 5 minutes each (after each running block)\n",
    "- **Final baseline phase**: 5 minutes rest before ending of the protocol\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "**Shoe Conditions (ABCCBA design):**\n",
    "- **A**: KipRun KipStorm Foam model\n",
    "- **B**: KipRun KipStorm Carbon model  \n",
    "- **C**: Prototype model (non-commercialized)\n",
    "\n",
    "**Running block sequence:**  \n",
    "Block 1: A (Foam) → Block 2: B (Carbon) → Block 3: C (Prototype) →  \n",
    "Block 4: C (Prototype) → Block 5: B (Carbon) → Block 6: A (Foam)\n",
    "\n",
    "### Measured Variables\n",
    "\n",
    "#### 1. Systemic Variables (Cosmed K5 + Heart Rate)\n",
    "- VO₂ (oxygen consumption, mL/min)\n",
    "- VCO₂ (carbon dioxide production, mL/min)\n",
    "- HR (heart rate, bpm)\n",
    "- RER (respiratory exchange ratio)\n",
    "- VE (minute ventilation, L/min)\n",
    "- VT (tidal volume, L)\n",
    "- FR (respiratory frequency, breaths/min)\n",
    "\n",
    "**Derived metrics:**\n",
    "- Energy cost per shoe condition\n",
    "- Running economy (VO₂ at steady-state)\n",
    "- Metabolic cost of running\n",
    "- Oxygen pulse = VO₂ / HR\n",
    "\n",
    "#### 2. Peripheral Variables (mNIRS)\n",
    "- SmO₂ (muscle oxygen saturation, %)\n",
    "- HbTot (total hemoglobin, μM)\n",
    "- HHb (deoxyhemoglobin, μM)\n",
    "- HbDiff (hemoglobin difference, μM)\n",
    "\n",
    "#### 3. Vertical Forces (Force Plate)\n",
    "- Peak force (given in V but to convert in N)\n",
    "- Step frequency (Hz)\n",
    "\n",
    "### Analysis Structure\n",
    "1. Data loading and synchronization\n",
    "2. Protocol segmentation (initial baseline + 6 runs + 5 recoveries + final baseline)\n",
    "3. Shoe condition assignment (A, B, C)\n",
    "4. Time series visualization with phase markers\n",
    "5. Extraction of steady-state values per running block\n",
    "6. Statistical comparison by shoe condition\n",
    "7. Visualization: boxplots, bar plots, comparative plots\n",
    "8. Final summary tables by shoe type\n"
   ]
  },
