    "## 10. Interpretation of Statistical Results\n",
    "\n",
    "### 10.1 Results-driven interpretation (A/B/C) :\n",
    "\n",
    "Using the current block-level summaries :\n",
    "\n",
    "- **Condition B (KipRun Carbon)** shows the highest metabolic demand in this participant:\n",
    "  - Highest mean VO2 (`~994 mL/min`)\n",
    "  - Highest cumulative VO2 demand (AUC `~401,024`)\n",
    "  - Very low within-condition variability (CV `~0.64%`), so this signal is internally consistent\n",
    "- **Condition C** shows the lowest mean VO2 (`~850 mL/min`), which could suggest better economy, **but** variability is very high (CV `~42.4%`), so this estimate is unstable.\n",
    "- **Condition A** is intermediate in VO2 (`~952 mL/min`) but has the lowest TSI (`~58.1`) and most negative HHb (`~ -3.0`), indicating stronger peripheral deoxygenation / oxygen extraction.\n",
    "\n",
    "### 10.2 Physiological expectation vs observed result :\n",
    "\n",
    "From a biomechanical perspective, a carbon-plated shoe is often expected to improve running economy through energy return and altered stiffness dynamics. In this dataset, however, the **observed participant-level response does not match that expectation**, because condition B appears more costly on VO2-based indicators.\n",
    "\n",
    "This is not necessarily contradictory to the theory: it may reflect subject-specific adaptation, protocol order effects, pacing behavior, fatigue interactions, or day-to-day physiological variability.\n",
    "\n",
    "### 10.3 Baseline-to-final state :\n",
    "\n",
    "Baseline comparison indicates a clear post-protocol shift:\n",
    "\n",
    "- VO2 decreases from `2236.6` to `1321.7` (`Δ ~ -914.9`)\n",
    "- TSI slightly decreases (`Δ ~ -0.76`)\n",
    "- HHb shifts downward (`Δ ~ -2.46`)\n",
    "\n",
    "This supports a marked physiological change between initial and final baseline windows.\n",
    "\n",
    "### 10.4 Inferential statistics (strength of evidence) :\n",
    "\n",
    "Despite descriptive differences between conditions, inferential tests remain non-significant:\n",
    "\n",
    "- **Repeated-measures ANOVA:** all reported p-values are > 0.05 (`VO2_mean p=0.79`, `VO2_auc p=0.70`, `TSI_slope p=0.51`, `HHb_slope p=0.68`)\n",
    "- **Bonferroni post-hoc:** all corrected p-values are non-significant\n",
    "- **Friedman robustness check:** non-significant for available repeated metrics (typically `p=0.61`, one at `p=0.22`)\n",
    "\n",
    "Interpretation: current differences are useful for exploratory profiling but are **not statistically confirmed** at this stage.\n",
    "\n",
    "### 10.5 Correlation structure :\n",
    "\n",
    "Pairwise block-level correlations are weak-to-moderate and non-significant:\n",
    "\n",
    "- VO2_mean vs TSI_mean: `r ~ +0.47`, `p=0.34`\n",
    "- VO2_mean vs HHb_mean: `r ~ -0.28`, `p=0.59`\n",
    "- TSI_mean vs Force_mean: `r ~ +0.27`, `p=0.61`\n",
    "\n",
    "No single peripheral marker fully explains metabolic cost in this dataset.\n",
    "\n",
    "### 10.6 Conclusion and next phase (n = 20) :\n",
    "\n",
    "**Current conclusion (single-participant, exploratory):**\n",
    "\n",
    "- In this participant, **condition B (carbon) is descriptively the most energy-costly profile** on VO2-based metrics.\n",
    "- This finding should be interpreted as an **individual response**, not a definitive statement about carbon footwear efficacy and other footwear conditions.\n",
    "\n",
    "**Prospective conclusion for the full study:**\n",
    "\n",
    "- The upcoming analyses on the planned **20 participants** may confirm, attenuate, or reverse this pattern.\n",
    "- Group-level inference will provide a more valid estimate of the true effect of shoe condition on energetic cost.\n",
    "- The final report should prioritize population-level estimates (effect sizes + confidence intervals + corrected p-values), while retaining individual-response profiles as secondary clinical/performance insight.\n",
    "\n",
    "### 10.7 Files used for interpretation :\n",
    "\n",
    "| CSV file | Role |\n",
    "| --- | --- |\n",
    "| `Advanced_Block_Level_Metrics.csv` | Per-block physiological descriptors |\n",
    "| `Advanced_Condition_Summary.csv` | Condition-level synthesis used for economy/cost ranking |\n",
    "| `Advanced_Baseline_Comparison.csv` | Initial vs final state changes |\n",
    "| `Advanced_ANOVA_Results.csv` | Omnibus condition-effect testing |\n",
    "| `Advanced_PostHoc_Bonferroni.csv` | Pairwise contrasts with multiplicity control |\n",
    "| `Advanced_Friedman_Results.csv` | Non-parametric robustness check |\n",
    "\n",
    "Correlation outputs are kept in the notebook (table + heatmap) to avoid redundant exports."
